Kytherion,<br>
<br>
I think you are absolutely correct.  A good number of those auto-companies would lose a lot of business, if they could not export to the United States.<br>
<br>
However, it just seemed like to me that Walterscott was trying to paint 'most other foreign' car companies as being heartless, cheap, and impolite bastards.<br>
<br>
It is an incredible thing to donate to this cause, but at the same time, it would really really surprise me if the big-3 <b>didn't</b> donate.  As a matter of fact, it also would not surprise me if one of the manufacturers donated, and the other two realized it would be bad PR not to donate.<br>
<br>
All-in-all, I am glad donations were made.  I am just unsure of the direction Walterscott was taking his remark.  Sounds like he is saying that the domestic automakers have hearts, and most of the import-automakers do not.<br>
<br>
*shrug*<br>
<br>
